Class PontoDiaModelImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.liferay.portal.kernel.model.impl.BaseModelImpl<PontoDia>
      • com.desafio.ponto.model.impl.PontoDiaModelImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PontoDiaModel, com.liferay.portal.kernel.model.BaseModel<PontoDia>, com.liferay.portal.kernel.model.ClassedModel, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<PontoDia>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PontoDiaBaseImpl

    @ProviderType
public class PontoDiaModelImpl
extends com.liferay.portal.kernel.model.impl.BaseModelImpl<PontoDia>
implements PontoDiaModel
    The base model implementation for the PontoDia service. Represents a row in the "ponto_dia" database table, with each column mapped to a property of this class.

    This implementation and its corresponding interface PontoDiaModel exist only as a container for the default property accessors generated by ServiceBuilder. Helper methods and all application logic should be put in PontoDiaImpl.

    Author:
    Peterson Morais
    See Also:
    PontoDiaImpl, PontoDia, PontoDiaModel, Serialized Form
